      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DARNUM STUMP (7) is rarely far away but tends to find one better, placing 10 from 18 starts. Has been in the minors the last two runs, the latest finishing second (19.69) at this track. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from four attempts. Capable of going well again. LINDEN BOOTS (2) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 1.5 lengths from the winner (19.76). A big run wouldn't surprise. ZAWADI (6) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by half a length at this track in a handy 19.67 beating DARNUM STUMP. Has hit winning form and can measure up again. BRONELLY TIMMY (3) has definite claims at his first try at this circuit.",
